by UIJ » Sat Feb 05, 2022 5:06 pm

Austria-Bohemia-Hungary wrote:No, because with current methods one cannot detect, let alone engage a submarine before it shoots and sinks you. Like, the playing field is in complete advantage to the submarine.

Also a complete submarine-based fleet for a minor country would be incredibly based... unlike the one where it tries to buy a tanker and fit three thousand Mk 41's to in order to invade somebody 6000 miles away with its nonexistent army.

Inherently false. Submarines can be detected before firing and have been many times. Additionally, surface fleets often are accompanied by their own submarines for the exact purpose of defending against hostile submarines, they’re constantly looking for other subs.

Submarines are also dogshit at anything other than anti-ship and anti-ground, they don’t have the radar for anti-air, they can’t really transport any cargo or troops, and quite frankly they can be incredibly slow, especially if they’re trying to hide. Relying on submarines to do everything is a fool’s errand.

Additionally there is technology being developed (satellite or ship-based LIDAR that can work underwater) that may make submarines obsolete, or at least easy to detect if they’re anywhere near the surface. Sonar and other forms of detection are only getting better, and if submarines are detected they have little in terms of defense and even a single hit can send them to the bottom with all hands.

Submarines are important, but don’t overestimate them.

Littoral Combat Ships. I would expect to see someone use something in the same vein as a LCS, given that people use battleships on here, but now that I think about it, I haven't seen any of that. You'd expect armchair navy enthusiasts on this site to have a collective violent orgasm at the sheer thought of using both failures in their navies against other people doing so in roleplay.
